<h3 class="teaser_headline"><a href="/features/qa/hiv-infant-feeding/en/index.html">HIV and infant feeding</a></h3> 
	
   
<div  class="image_left"  >
		<a href="/features/qa/hiv-infant-feeding/en/index.html">
<img src="/features/qa/25502185252_627b72041b_o_hp.jpg" alt="" width="310" height="200" />
<div class="image_credit">WHO</div>
</a>
</div>
 
<p>
	<span> 11 August 2016 -- WHO recommends that all mothers living with HIV should receive life-long antiretroviral therapy (ART) to support their health and to ensure the wellbeing of their infants. New WHO guidelines advise mothers living with HIV who are on ART and adherent to therapy to breastfeed exclusively for the first 6 months, and then add complementary feeding until 12 months of age.</span>
</p>	
